  "prompt": "How do I play mkv files on Samsung tv?",
  "response": "To play MKV files on a Samsung TV, you have several options:\n\n1. USB Method:\n- Connect a USB drive with MKV files\n- Use the TV's built-in media player\n- Select the MKV file from the USB drive\n- Some Samsung TVs support MKV playback directly\n\n2. Screen Mirroring/Casting:\n- Use screen mirroring from a smartphone or laptop\n- Cast MKV files using apps like AllShare or SmartView\n- Ensure your TV and device are on the same Wi-Fi network\n\n3. DLNA Streaming:\n- Use media server software like Plex or Kodi\n- Stream MKV files from a computer to your Samsung TV\n\n4. Convert MKV Files:\n- Use video conversion software to convert MKV to MP4\n- Choose formats compatible with Samsung TVs\n\n5. Smart TV Apps:\n- Use media player apps like Plex or Media Player\n- Download from Samsung App Store\n\n6. External Media Players:\n- Use devices like Chromecast, Roku, or Amazon Fire TV\n- These often have better MKV compatibility\n\nTip: Check your specific Samsung TV model's compatibility, as features can vary between models.",
